e shown, loaded from which providers\n46\t- **Interactions** — Taps (push detail), swipes (dismiss, page), pulls (refresh), long-press (context menu)\n47\t- **Transitions** — How user arrives (push, tab switch, bottom sheet present) and leaves (pop, swipe back)\n48\t\n49\t### Part 4: Navigation Architecture\n50\t- **Navigator structure** — GoRouter with ShellRoute for bottom nav\n51\t- **Bottom Navigation** — Tab destinations (3-5), icons, labels\n52\t- **Push routes** — Card tap → detail screen, list item → reader\n53\t- **Modal routes** — Bottom sheets for quick actions, dialogs for confirmations\n54\t- **Deep links** — URI patterns for each route\n55\t\n56\t### Part 5: Data Context\n57\t- Entity list with key fields\n58\t- Relationships between entities\n59\t- Which screens consume which entities\n60\t\n61\t### Part 6: Design Tokens\n62\t- Color palette recommendations (Material 3 seed color)\n63\t- Typography scale (Google Fonts recommendation)\n64\t- Spacing rhythm (base 8dp)\n65\t- Corner radius scale\n66\t- Elevation levels (Material 3 tonal elevation)\n67\t- Animation curves and durations\n68\t\n69\t## Flutter Mobile Design Principles\n70\t\n71\t- Every screen is a `Scaffold` — AppBar, body, optional bottom nav and FAB\n72\t- Bottom navigation for primary destinations (max 5 tabs) using `ShellRoute`\n73\t- Detail screens push on top of the navigation stack (`context.push`)\n74\t- Quick actions use bottom sheets (`showModalBottomSheet`), not separate screens\n75\t- Tab content uses `DefaultTabController` + `TabBar` + `TabBarView`\n76\t- Scrollable lists use `CustomScrollView` with `SliverAppBar` for collapsing headers\n77\t- Pull-to-refresh via `RefreshIndicator` on scrollable content\n78\t- Safe areas respected — content never hidden behind system UI\n79\t- Touch targets minimum 48dp — all tappable elements\n80\t- Thumb zone awareness — primary actions in bottom half of screen\n81\t- Horizontal scroll for category chips, carousels, and content previews\n82\t- Hero animations for shared-element transitions between list and detail\n83\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e890309f-5b52-4dea-a8e6-50a58bec8afb","uuid":"ace01293-6405-4c5f-85cf-0518b564dc8e","timestamp":"2026-05-18T15:00:44.553Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.converge/skills/ux-design/SKILL.md","content":"# UX Design Skill\n\nGenerate a complete UX specification for a Flutter mobile application. Think natively in mobile — Scaffolds, navigators, gestures, bottom sheets — not web pages adapted for small screens.\n\n## Inputs\n\n- `PRD.md` — Product Requirements Document\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. **Read PRD** — Understand the app's purpose, features, user personas\n2. **Define Vibe** — Establish the visual personality (e.g., \"warm literary\", \"sleek minimal\", \"playful bright\")\n3. **Design Screens** — Define each screen as a Flutter Scaffold with:\n   - Purpose and user intent\n   - Scaffold chrome (AppBar, BottomNavigationBar, FAB)\n   - Body layout and scroll behavior\n   - Data displayed\n   - User interactions and gestures\n   - Navigation flows (push, pop, present sheet)\n4. **Data Context** — List data entities and relationships\n5. **Design Tokens** — Recommend colors, typography, spacing, motion\n\n## Output\n\nWrite `.stitch/UX.md` with these sections:\n\n### Part 1: Project Overview\n- App name, description, platform (Flutter mobile)\n- Core identity (3-4 adjectives)\n- User personas summary\n\n### Part 2: Vibe\n- Visual atmosphere description\n- Color mood (warm/cool, light/dark)\n- Typography character (modern/classic, rounded/sharp)\n- Motion personality (bouncy/smooth, fast/gentle)\n\n### Part 3: Screens\nFor each screen:\n- **Name** and GoRouter route\n- **Purpose** — Why this screen exists\n- **Scaffold** — AppBar config, bottom nav visibility, FAB placement\n- **Body** — Scroll type (ListView, CustomScrollView with Slivers, PageView, none)\n- **Sections** — Visual blocks within the body\n- **Data** — What entities are shown, loaded from which providers\n- **Interactions** — Taps (push detail), swipes (dismiss, page), pulls (refresh), long-press (context menu)\n- **Transitions** — How user arrives (push, tab switch, bottom sheet present) and leaves (pop, swipe back)\n\n### Part 4: Navigation Architecture\n- **Navigator structure** — GoRouter with ShellRoute for bottom nav\n- **Bottom Navigation** — Tab destinations (3-5), icons, labels\n- **Push routes** — Card tap → detail screen, list item → reader\n- **Modal routes** — Bottom sheets for quick actions, dialogs for confirmations\n- **Deep links** — URI patterns for each route\n\n### Part 5: Data Context\n- Entity list with key fields\n- Relationships between entities\n- Which screens consume which entities\n\n### Part 6: Design Tokens\n- Color palette recommendations (Material 3 seed color)\n- Typography scale (Google Fonts recommendation)\n- Spacing rhythm (base 8dp)\n- Corner radius scale\n- Elevation levels (Material 3 tonal elevation)\n- Animation curves and durations\n\n## Flutter Mobile Design Principles\n\n- Every screen is a `Scaffold` — AppBar, body, optional bottom nav and FAB\n- Bottom navigation for primary destinations (max 5 tabs) using `ShellRoute`\n- Detail screens push on top of the navigation stack (`context.push`)\n- Quick actions use bottom sheets (`showModalBottomSheet`), not separate screens\n- Tab content uses `DefaultTabController` + `TabBar` + `TabBarView`\n- Scrollable lists use `CustomScrollView` with `SliverAppBar` for collapsing headers\n- Pull-to-refresh via `RefreshIndicator` on scrollable content\n- Safe areas respected — content never hidden behind system UI\n- Touch targets minimum 48dp — all tappable elements\n- Thumb zone awareness — primary actions in bottom half of screen\n- Horizontal scroll for category chips, carousels, and content previews\n- Hero animations for shared-element transitions between list and detail\n","numLines":83,"startLine":1,"totalLines":83}}}
[2026-05-18T15:00:44.556Z] [TOOL_RESULT] 1	# UX Design Skill
2	
3	Generate a complete UX specification for a Flutter mobile application. Think natively in mobile — Scaffolds, navigators, gestures, bottom sheets — not web pages adapted for small screens.
4	
5	## Inputs
6	
7	- `PRD.md` — Product Requirements Document
8	
9	## Procedure
10	
11	1. **Read PRD** — Understand the app's purpose, features, user personas
12	2. **Define Vibe** — Establish the visual personality (e.g., "warm literary", "sleek minimal", "playful bright")
13	3. **Design Screens** — Define each screen as a Flutter Scaffold with:
14	   - Purpose and user intent
15	   - Scaffold chrome (AppBar, BottomNavigationBar, FAB)
16	   - Body layout and scroll behavior
17	   - Data displayed
18	   - User interactions and gestures
19	   - Navigation flows (push, pop, present sheet)
20	4. **Data Context** — List data entities and relationships
21	5. **Design Tokens** — Recommend colors, typography, spacing, motion
22	
23	## Output
24	
25	Write `.stitch/UX.md` with these sections:
26	
27	### Part 1: Project Overview
28	- App name, description, platform (Flutter mobile)
29	- Core identity (3-4 adjectives)
30	- User personas summary
31	
32	### Part 2: Vibe
33	- Visual atmosphere description
34	- Color mood (warm/cool, light/dark)
35	- Typography character (modern/classic, rounded/sharp)
36	- Motion personality (bouncy/smooth, fast/gentle)
37	
38	### Part 3: Screens
39	For each screen:
40	- **Name** and GoRouter route
41	- **Purpose** — Why this screen exists
42	- **Scaffold** — AppBar config, bottom nav visibility, FAB placement
43	- **Body** — Scroll type (ListView, CustomScrollView with Slivers, PageView, none)
44	- **Sections** — Visual blocks within the body
45	- **Data** — What entities are shown, loaded from which providers
46	- **Interactions** — Taps (push detail), swipes (dismiss, page), pulls (refresh), long-press (context menu)
47	- **Transitions** — How user arrives (push, tab switch, bottom sheet present) and leaves (pop, swipe back)
48	
49	### Part 4: Navigation Architecture
50	- **Navigator structure** — GoRouter with ShellRoute for bottom nav
51	- **Bottom Navigation** — Tab destinations (3-5), icons, labels
52	- **Push routes** — Card tap → detail screen, list item → reader
53	- **Modal routes** — Bottom sheets for quick actions, dialogs for confirmations
54	- **Deep links** — URI patterns for each route
55	
56	### Part 5: Data Context
57	- Entity list with key fields
58	- Relationships between entities
59	- Which screens consume which entities
60	
61	### Part 6: Design Tokens
62	- Color palette recommendations (Material 3 seed color)
63	- Typography scale (Google Fonts recommendation)
64	- Spacing rhythm (base 8dp)
65	- Corner radius scale
66	- Elevation levels (Material 3 tonal elevation)
67	- Animation curves and durations
68	
69	## Flutter Mobile Design Principles
70	
71	- Every screen is a `Scaffold` — AppBar, body, optional bottom nav and FAB
72	- Bottom navigation for primary destinations (max 5 tabs) using `ShellRoute`
73	- Detail screens push on top of the navigation stack (`context.push`)
74	- Quick actions use bottom sheets (`showModalBottomSheet`), not separate screens
75	- Tab content uses `DefaultTabController` + `TabBar` + `TabBarView`
76	- Scrollable lists use `CustomScrollView` with `SliverAppBar` for collapsing headers
77	- Pull-to-refresh via `RefreshIndicator` on scrollable content
78	- Safe areas respected — content never hidden behind system UI
79	- Touch targets minimum 48dp — all tappable elements
80	- Thumb zone awareness — primary actions in bottom half of screen
81	- Horizontal scroll for category chips, carousels, and content previews
82	- Hero animations for shared-element transitions between list and detail
83	
